column5: How tough it is to communicate sometimes. I wish they would be a little more sensitive to that
I struggle with weight too. I think a lot of schizophrenics do because of medication side effects. I’ll try the walking aerobics, sounds convenient. Good luck!
I could see this being maybe heaven and hell too. Awesome work !
I have been feeling better lately too, but not too much better. Just enough where I know it’s not mania. But hey I guess that’s for the pdoc to decide
Love the eye in the sky
Yea I can relate to that. Actually going through it at the moment
I went here in the summer of 2013. Did some cliff diving too!
Do you have any family that you get support from too?
It’s very weird and can also be utterly disturbing when you come to
I don’t desire socializing either. I can’t remember the last time I really wanted to go out on my free time
